formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1.	Actual cost of construction incurred as per books of accounts included therein cost incurred in the nature of ?on- Site expenditure in the nature of development of project? and ?Payment of Taxes ?.
2.	The firm had not maintained separate RERA Account. 
3.	In the absence of specific guideline regarding interest on capital paid by the firm to the partners, it was included in estimated as well as cost incurred and paid at the time of applying for registration and thereafter in quarterly compliance made under RERA upto 31/05/2019. However, after issue of Guidance note-1 dated 09-07-2019 I have reduced the interest cost on partner?s capital from the cost incurred and paid. 
4.	In respect of the units for which the date of AFS is mentioned, I would like to clarify that the firm is not in possession of Agreement to sale details and in absence of information, I have mentioned the date of sale deed executed instead of date of agreement to sale. Further, I am unable to certify as to whether the firm had entered registered Agreement for Sale with buyers on receipt of consideration in excess of 10% of the apartment value.
5.	In respect of the units for which date of agreement to sale is kept blank, the firm has not executed registered agreement of sale.
6.	I am unable to certify the date of sale deed execution, PAN no and Mobile Number of the customer, since the necessary evidence is not in the possession of the firm.
7. The firm had also deposited booking receipt of Rs 11927550 in account maintained with SBI , commercial branch,surat bearing account no 37598283357.
